retweet.text:
üö® TESLA + STARLINK = INTERNET EVERYWHERE (YES, EVEN IN THE MIDDLE OF NOWHERE)

Tesla just got the green light from the FCC to use Starlink terminals on moving vehicles‚Ä¶ aka, satellite internet in your car is officially on the way.

Basically, Tesla filed a patent covering a vehicle roof assembly that is transparent to radio frequencies, specifically noting that it allows for satellite communications to pass through.

That's important, as signals from SpaceX satellites can't reliably penetrate glass or metal.

This project isn‚Äôt theoretical either, it means Teslas could soon have an always-on, high-speed internet powered by SpaceX‚Äôs global Starlink network.

Forget losing signal in remote areas, your car could stream Netflix in the desert, get OTA updates in the mountains, or run Full Self-Driving with real-time data literally anywhere on Earth.

If you thought Teslas were already futuristic, this is next level.

We still don't know when or if this is coming to Tesla vehicles, but the patent filing is our best sign yet that it's coming soon.

Source: InsideEVs, @tesla @Starlink
